# Three related manifests (Sage observation ≠ mathematics ≠ interpretation)
# ========================================================================
#
#   observed Sage @ version v
#   +  normalized graph 𝒢
#   +  Sage → normalized correspondence
#   →  generated Graphviz views
#
# Neither Sage nor correspondence duplicates normalized definitions.
#
# Decision record 3 §6: the generated Graphviz views (correspondence.dot,
# observed_parents.dot, category_parent_graph.{dot,svg,html}) and any large
# snapshot are NON-AUTHORITATIVE — CI artifacts / review attachments, never a
# coequal source of mathematical truth. Truth is the normalized SSOT
# (semantic_seed/) and the DR3 §6.3 bridge records; the hand parent DOT is an
# archived requirements inventory (see category_parent_graph.hand.dot), frozen.

design/
  schemas/                 # JSON Schema for the three manifests (+ routes)
  normalized/
    manifest/              # → semantic_seed/ (entities, classifiers, arrows)
  sage/
    runtime_probe.json     # GENERATED live category_sample / super_categories
    observed.json          # GENERATED empirical snapshot (no math corrections)
    mapping.yaml           # REVIEWED correspondence (categories/edges/axioms/…)
    correspondence.dot     # GENERATED bipartite view
    observed_parents.dot   # GENERATED raw Sage parent graph

  routes/
    routes.yaml            # optional execution routing (separate from meaning)
  normalized_category_graph/   # presentation DOT + hand archive (legacy path)
  sage_category_graph/         # inventory sources feeding observed.json
  sage_to_normalized_map/      # legacy correspondence.json (loaded via mapping)

Contracts
---------
1. Observed Sage
   - Auto-extracted from pinned Sage source/runtime inventory.
   - Records classes, parameters, immediate supercategories, axioms,
     constructions, aliases — as Sage reports them.
   - Does NOT classify property/structure/stuff; does NOT “fix” parents.

2. Normalized graph
   - Mathematical SSOT: category *expressions* (roots, refine, names) and
     classifiers at least hosts.
   - Ordinary hierarchy functors are **generated** (classifier legs +
     projection composites by structural recursion), not hand-authored.
   - Vault: decisions/category-expressions-generate-projection-hierarchy.
   - Sage mapping refers to expression/named ids; edge checks expand from the
     target’s projection spine.

3. Correspondence
   - Hand-authored/reviewed; mechanically validated against (1) and (2).
   - category_mappings.relation ∈
       {exact, presentation_alias, canonical_equivalence,
        corrected_embedding, constructible, unsupported, removed}
   - ``constructible``: Sage Base.A… is an ephemeral classifier tower over a
     normalized base C (C must be a node; each Ai's host reachable from C).
     The full C.A1.A2… need not be a literal named vertex of 𝒢.
   - Every Sage immediate-supercategory edge needs a disposition
       {preserved, subdivided, corrected, alias_artifact, unsupported}.
   - axiom_mappings target clf.*; construction_mappings target con.*.

4. Routes (optional)
   - op.* → Sage method receivers; versioned separately from category meaning.

Maintenance
-----------
Sage v → v+1:
  1. just manifests-probe   # runtime_probe.json + observed.json + mapping.yaml
  2. just manifests-diff path/to/observed-v.yaml   # structural diff
  3. just audit manifests   # hygiene (edge dispositions complete)
  4. just audit manifests-parity   # fails while unsupported rows remain
  5. edit only affected mapping entries / version overlays
  6. just seed-dot / just manifests
Normalized graph changes only when mathematics changes.

CLI
---
  just manifests-probe   live Sage dump + rebuild
  just manifests         rebuild from existing probe/inventory
  just manifests-diff X  diff observed X → current
  just audit manifests
  just audit manifests-parity
